@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Coulisso" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  The game is played on game boards of various sizes, in which
different numbers of coloured bars are placed on diagonal path
sections. The idea is to move bars following path sections so they
are placed on the same space. When 2 bars are on the same path
section, these 'explode' and the path section, where the bars were
located, will become a 'hole' which will become impassable...

  Some path sections are 'turntables', so they can rotate by 90
degrees. These have trapezoidal shapes on either side. This type of
path section will rotate if a bar is located on it and/or another
bar is not immediately next and in line with that path section.

  To move a bar, click on a path section that is located next and
in line with the bar. If 2 bars are on either side of the clicked
path section, these bars will move together and then will be
eliminated... The same thing happens if the path section was
already occupied by a bar and one or 2 bars occupy neighbouring
path sections.

  Do not accidentally isolate bars, which will make the game
impossible to complete. If that happens, click on the 'Replay'
button to restart that game board. Note that everytime you restart
a game board, an extra move is added and the total number of moves
accumulates until you complete it...

  You can change the colour of the bars, by clicking on the
'Colour' button.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

